{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, since LLMs are pre-trained to predict the next word in a sentence, some research groups fine-tuned them also to predict future sensor events [24,44].",
    "2.2.2Zero-shot approaches for human activity recognition using LLMs.",
    "Similarly to ADL-LLM, other works aim at recognizing human activities using LLMs without any training phase.",
    "For instance, some works show that LLMs can reason on raw inertial sensor data from mobile/wearable devices to distinguish between a limited set of low-level physical activities [28,32].",
    "Another line of research leverages a pre-trained model generating 3D motion sequences from text [51] to generate synthetic labeled data from wearable/mobile devices [34]."
  ]
}